Email Generator and Sender using Gemini AI Model
Overview
This script uses a pre-trained Gemini AI model to generate a more formal message from a user's input and sends the improved message as an email to a specified recipient.

Requirements
Python 3.x
google.generativeai library (install with pip install google-generativeai)
A Gemini API key (replace YOUR_GOOGLE_GEMINI_API_KEY with your actual API key)
Usage
Run the script using Python (e.g., python script.py)
Enter your email address, password, recipient's email address, and a message when prompted
The script will generate a more formal message using the Gemini AI model and send it to the recipient
Script Components
send_email function: sends an email using the provided sender, password, recipient, and message
main function: gets user input, generates a more formal message using the Gemini AI model, and sends the email
Note
Make sure to replace YOUR_GOOGLE_GEMINI_API_KEY with your actual Gemini API key
This script uses a simple email sending mechanism and may not work with all email providers or configurations
Be cautious when entering your email password, as it is stored in plain text in this script
